===Usage Notes===
''Tāwai'' and ''Tāwan'' (which decline the same as [[Dēiwas]]), the [[feminine]] and [[neuter]] forms of ''Tāwas'' (''father'', which by definition refers to a male), respectively, are grammatically possible but never used except as insults.

